description.narrative: UNICEF coordination of the sectors at the Whole of Syria and the hub levels is managed efficiently and effectively, which contributes to Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Operations Support To Programme Delivery, Operations Support To Programme Delivery (Covid), Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: MENARO delivers timely, equitable and principled humanitarian action as a complement to country office-led operations where required, including through the cross-border component of the Syria programmes as part of the Whole of Syria response.

description.narrative: During year 2019,UNICEF has maintained operational Whole of Syria and cross border capacity both through staffing and resource mobilization.UNICEF has continued to support effective cross border programmes andSector coordination for WASH,Nutrition,Education and Child Protection(as an Area of Responsibility).UNICEF programmes have targeted populations in greatest need through national/international cluster partners.UNICEF has invested in coordination and to develop capacities of the different humanitarian stakeholders and leveraged its resources to address humanitarian needs.Throughout all the year,UNICEF has used its cluster lead obligations and its strategic engagement at several level(SSG,HLG,ISG,ICCG),as a leveraging power to promote its value related to equity,gender and protection of rights | Status:On-track | As-of Date:09/04/2020
